        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=6597&FORUM_ID=11&CAT_ID=5&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=The+Adventures+of+Apprentice+Zrren"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Greeting's..Ive started an Erudite Necro and am throughly enjoying the heck out of playing him. As a 31 Enchanter, 30 Shadowknight, 18 Shaman ive played the same old route, newbie zone, Q hills, Oasis, Highpass Hold, GuardRoom in the Keep for lvling, BUT i must say, starting in Paineel was a pleasure lots of skellys in the noobie area, and a dark and relaxing cities to wonder round in. I ventured to Qeynos at lvl 6, and did solo there till 12, then went to eruds crossing and hunted the wisps, good exp and lots of Greater Light Stones. Heading to the Gypsies in NK, I traded in the GLS for COR, and sold them back, getting nuff PP to buy the remaining lvl 12 spells, now instead of the same old boring zones to lvl in, i utilized the hunting guide(wonderful tool guys many thanks) and decided on Kurns Tower in FOB. I had taken my SK "Xaelwyn" there to scout the Overthere, Warsliks Woods, and FOB. so Zrrens journey to Kurns Tower was easy and fast, thanks to a nice Druid in OT. arriving in KT I bound outside, zoned in, cast invis vs Undead and went right to the hidden room on the first floor, cast pet, gave him a Halbrad and got right to work. took out a couple of blues and even con, thru caution to the wind and began pulling Yellow cons. well I got a little overzelous and had an add which was yellow, but by the end of the fight pet was at 1/4 life, i had a smidge of red in hp, and OOM, i was amazed I survived, and even more impressed with thes lvl12 pet hitting for 20.</P><P>after 16, i have no intention of returning to my old lvling habbits, but will go to the Mud pit(that what we callit on 7th hammer) in OT,  at 19 or 20 head off to Lake of Illomen till 29 or 30, then back to OT for great Experience, NOW if you My evil friends would suggest some NPC hunting as a break between Kurns Tower and the mud pit, mud pit to FM ledge, i would greatly appreacite it.</P><P>For Evilzor: if you see this post Please shot me an E-mail or post here, my other Char are in Guardians of the Sacred ALtar, but would like to consider joining an evil guild,(when i arrive at apport lvl, and meet any requirements) if you have any ideas, i would be interested in hearing them</P><P>Zrren<BR>12th Necromancer on 7th Hammer</P><P></P><P>Edited by - Zrren on 08/16/2001  13:25:44</font></td>
      </tr>

