        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=51171&TOPIC_ID=6597&FORUM_ID=11&CAT_ID=5&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=The+Adventures+of+Apprentice+Zrren&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>


        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">Greeting Masters, I arrived at Kurns Tower this morning, pulled bone chips from my pouch, threw them to the floor and recited the words of summoning, bring forth "Vebaner" from the lower realms, much to my dismay he appeared a weakly sort of companion, as i was about to dismiss him and resummon, he turned to me, and begged to stay and serve me. I was apprenhisive, to say the least. I eventually gave him my weapon of choice a two handed Halbard. enchanced his strength and conjoured up my own enhancments. After the required Medition, I set out to find a worthy opponent, a long search wasnot required as I emerged from my darkened chamber to find the main hall full of prey. Casting Darkness and bringing the prey back to Vebaner, he grinned evily and went to work eager to show his worth. Ahhh, what a surprise forhe slashed the enemy for 20 points of damage repeatdly.<BR>Again and again did Vebaner and I stand side by side as Scalebone and Greater Skeletons fell. In total did 18 green, 57 blue, 10 black, and 6 yellow conned opponents fall beneath my magic and Dragoon Dirk.</P><P>After a weary day, I returned to the Evil oupost in The Overthere to sell my spoils, tally the wealth and experience to my pleasure I earned 16 platinum and advanced from the 12th to the 14th season. </P><P>May the Masters be Praised for thier insight</P><P>Zrren Apprentice Necromancer<BR>7th Hammer</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
